snippet.textDisplay:
Instagram 28k @JulianTattooer
Hows it going, here is a little background .
I started this journey when I was 14, teaching myself to tattoo after nearly failing for years.
I succeeded and now I specialize in all styles, and cover ups. The road was anything but easy, 13 years of tattooing trying the get ahead and I finally have. I have had My work Posted By Inked Magazine and other Large Social Media . Im 27 now & I own Power Ink Tattoos in Tampa Bay Florida. I enjoy my independent life, some how I have hacked not having to work a 9-5 or a job I can say . This leaves me a lot of time to enjoy life for what it is and to see aspects that people get epiphany's of on there off weekends questioning the idea the way jobs, rent, and pay and how drinking is used to control us as a whole . My family and I see life differently and I don't believe were meant to live the way we do. So for them and the one life we are given ,I do appointment only and we do welI , I guess feeling i'm attempting to get across is that I have no interest in changing for the industry or a label, for the music and I have no interest in changing my familys life over something that's not meaning full to us. Right now I spend my days doing half sleeves , an occasionally back piece and making music . Meaning I will entertain it to make my music and my self better as an artist. However I wont sign my life away for a check. I would much rather be in the mountains and build a studio there. Which I will one day. Right now I have a son on the way and I know the work will increasingly get better . Just like my Tattooing did. So i'm committed and if you are to as a fan, I promise you a journey.
Anyways, I wanted to spread my message through music with my love for hip hop so this is my life and i started writing it down 3 years ago. I Mix and produce all my own music. Dm JULIANTATTOOER ON INSTAGRAM for 20% off my work. Books open till dec.
Equipment
Mic: T103 Neuman
Audio Interface : Apollo Duo
Software: logic

Hows it going, here is a little background .
I started this journey when I was 14, teaching myself to tattoo after nearly failing for years. 
I succeeded and now I specialize in all styles, and cover ups.  The road was anything but easy, 13 years of tattooing trying the get ahead and I finally have. I have had My work Posted By Inked Magazine and other Large Social Media . Im 27 now & I own Power Ink Tattoos in Tampa Bay Florida. I enjoy my independent life, some how I have hacked not having to work a 9-5 or a job I can say . This leaves me a lot of time to enjoy life for what it is and to see aspects that people get epiphany's  of on there off weekends questioning the idea the way jobs, rent, and pay and how drinking is used to control us as a whole . My family and I see life differently and I don't believe were meant to live the way we do. So for them and the one life we are given ,I do appointment only and we do welI , I guess feeling i'm attempting to get across is that I have no interest in changing for the industry or a label, for the music and I have no interest in changing my familys life over something that's not meaning full to us. Right now I spend my days doing half sleeves , an occasionally back piece and making music .  Meaning I will entertain it to make my music and my self better as an artist. However I wont sign my life away for a check. I would much rather be in the mountains and build a studio there. Which I will one day. Right now I have a son on the way and I know the work will increasingly get better . Just like my Tattooing did. So i'm committed and if you are to as a fan, I promise you a journey.
Anyways, I wanted to spread my message through music with my love for hip hop so this is my life and i started writing it down 3 years ago. I Mix and produce all my own music. Dm JULIANTATTOOER ON INSTAGRAM for 20% off my work. Books open till dec.
